race.comment: LATORIO (10) tries hard in her races and is still chasing her first win after 11 starts. She was runner-up here two runs back before finishing sixth over 1619m last time out, 3 weeks ago over a mile. She is well placed in this field, and with the drop to a sprint trip this time, she could break through. SUMMER MOOD (9) was on the pace throughout and stuck on well for third over 1117m here last start, making it three straight minor placings. She faces a similar field, and should be about the money again. CALEB (4) ran a close second here last start over 1117m, beaten by just a head, and he will be peaking third up from a spell. He cops a tough gate, but can go one better. ALLA PING (12) made a promising debut, finishing not far away in fourth over 1117m at this track, and looks like the pacemaker again in this field. Stick with her. WRITTEN WORDS (5) resumes from a spell after a winning trial at Belmont by 4 lengths. He has drawn wide, but with Patrick Carbery riding, he can win this.
